INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('December2.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>

	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

	<title>Steam - Update</title>

	<link href="message10.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> </head>

<body>

	<div class="steamMessage">

	<h1>Friday, December 2 2005</h1><Br>

	We''ve been having fun the past few days playing on Internet <a href="steam://store/300">Day of Defeat: Source</a> servers on the new map "Argentan," and on <a href="steam://store/240">Counter-Strike: Source</a>''s updated version of de_nuke. So far both maps have been really well received - we''re glad everyone is enjoying them as much as we are. Next up on the Counter-Strike: Source front will be the release of two new player models.<br>

	<br>	

	This week on Steam, <a href="steam://store/1500">Darwinia</a> became available for pre-purchase at a discount of 10% off the full price, $19.95 USD. (This discount will remain in effect until the game is released on December 14th.) We''re really excited to ship this title. Hint: don''t make too many plans for December 15th, because you''ll be tired from staying up all night. Here''s <a href="http://storefront.steampowered.com/video/darwinia-steam.wmv">a video preview of Darwinia in action</a> (52MB).<br>

	<br>	

	The folks over at Ritual also have been keeping the community up to date with the development of the Sin Episodes. There are a couple of in-game screenshots below, and more over at <a target="_new" href="http://www.sinepisodes.com/">their site</a>. <br>

	<br>

	<a target="_new" href="December2.2005/img/sinepisodes_docks1.jpg"><img width="200" height="150" src="December2.2005/img/sinepisodes_docks1_thumb.jpg"></a> &nbsp; <a target="_new" href="December2.2005/img/sinepisodes_docks2.jpg"><img width="200" height="150" src="December2.2005/img/sinepisodes_docks2_thumb.jpg"></a>

	<br>

	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Steam, and the Steam logo are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation. All other trademarks are property of their respective owners.</span>

	</div>

</body>



</html>































































































































































































































<!--

     _

 ___| |___

|___   ___|

   _| |_

  |  _  |

  | | | |

  |_| |_|



-->

');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('December9.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"
        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>
	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">
	<title>Steam - Update</title>
	<link href="message10.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> </head>
<body>
	<div class="steamMessage">
	<h1>Friday, December 9 2005</h1><Br>
	<div style="background:#2f3527;padding:12px;">
		Hi, this is Gabe Newell. Normally the weekly Steam update news is written collaboratively by a number of people around Valve, but this week I''m grabbing the reins and writing it myself.<br>
		<br>
	<a target="_new" href="December9.2005/img/Darwinia_Temple.jpg"><img style="margin-right:12px;" align="left" width="200" height="150" src="December9.2005/img/Darwinia_Temple_thumb.jpg"></a> I''ve been playing a lot of Darwinia lately. Like most of you reading this, I play a lot of games and most of them don''t manage to capture my attention for very long. But I''m now playing through Darwinia a second time, so I think it''s fair to say I''m hooked. I''m currently on <i>Temple</i>, and while I''m not as good at the game as some people around the office, I''ve managed to get Airstrike researched to level 4.0 which is pretty satisfying. It''ll be out on Steam this coming Wednesday, and the demo will be available shortly before its launch. Send an e-mail to me at gaben@valvesoftware.com and tell me what you think of the game once you''ve played it.<br>
	</div>
	<hr>
	We recently had several members of the hardware press out to to Valve to see the new Day of Defeat movie we used to drive some new features in the Source engine. A number of articles about their visit should surface over the next week or so. The first one we''ve seen is over at <a target="_new" href="http://www.bit-tech.net/gaming/2005/12/09/source_film_effects/">Bit-Tech.net</a>.<br>
	<br>
	
	<br>
	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Steam, and the Steam logo are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation. All other trademarks are property of their respective owners.</span>
	</div>
</body>

</html>















































































































<!--
     _
 ___| |___
|___   ___|
   _| |_
  |  _  |
  | | | |
  |_| |_|

-->');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('December16.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"
        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>
	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">
	<title>Steam - Update</title>
	<link href="message10.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> </head>
<body>
	<div class="steamMessage">
	<h1>Friday, December 16 2005</h1><Br>

We have one more week of releases coming to Steam before we close out 2005. Next week there will be two new player models, one for each team, released for Counter-Strike: Source. Early next year we''ll be releasing a completely rebuilt version of cs_militia. There is also a fairly high chance we''ll be releasing an update to Day of Defeat: Source next week, which will include a number of small changes.<br>
<br>
<a target="_new" href="December16.2005/img/CSS_Seal_Team_6.jpg"><img width="200" height="121" src="December16.2005/img/CSS_Seal_Team_6_thumb.jpg"></a><br>
<br>
Earlier this week Darwinia was launched, and from what we''ve gathered, people are really enjoying the game. If you''re not sure if Darwinia is for you, check out the demo <a href="steam://store/1500">here</a>.<br>
<br>
We''d also like to congratulate the folks over at <a target="_new" href="http://www.darwinia.co.uk/">Introversion Software</a> for Darwinia''s <a target="_new" href="http://www.igf.com/2006entrants.shtml">4 nominations</a> at next year''s Independent Games Festival. As we''ve mentioned a number of times, we''re all huge fans of the game, and it''s great to see the game get the recognition it deserves.<br>

	<br>
	
	<br>
	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Steam, and the Steam logo are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation. All other trademarks are property of their respective owners.</span>
	</div>
</body>

</html>















































































































<!--
     _
 ___| |___
|___   ___|
   _| |_
  |  _  |
  | | | |
  |_| |_|

-->');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('December23.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>

	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

	<title>Steam - Update</title>

	<link href="message10.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> </head>

<body>

	<div class="steamMessage">

	<h1>Friday, December 23 2005</h1><Br>



This was a busy week for us as far as releases were concerned, with updates to Counter-Strike: Source, the Source engine running in 64 bit, and Day of Defeat: Source. We hope everyone is enjoying the new content. The plan is to keep releasing updates and new games next year.<br>

<br>

There are literally millions of people in the community that connect to Steam each month, so we compiled a couple of statistics for what has happened in the past year:<br>

	<ul>

		<li>Steam has delivered approximately 10 million gigabytes of data since the first of the year. You could fill 125,000 80 GB hard drives with this data to make a line over 11 miles long. Not that you would want to, but the visual helps.</li> 

	    <li>There have been a total of 50 billion player minutes in our multiplayer games since the start of the year. If a single person sat down to play on their own, it would take 2.28 million years to accomplish this. This is assuming that you''re not planning on sleeping during this 2 million year stretch.</li>

	</ul>

	<br>

	

	<br>

	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Steam, and the Steam logo are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation. All other trademarks are property of their respective owners.</span>

	</div>

</body>



</html>

');
