INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('Feb3.2006', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>

	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

	<title>Steam - Update</title>

	<link href="message12.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> 

</head>

<body>

	<div class="steamMessage">

	<h1>Friday, February 3 2006</h1><Br>

	Congratulations to <i>Dangerous Waters</i> for being recognized as IGN''s Game of the Month. You can head over <a target="_new" href="http://pc.ign.com/articles/684/684801p1.html">here</a> to read their writeup.  To check out <i>Dangerous Waters</i> or <i>Space Empires 4 Deluxe</i> as soon as they are available, preload and pre-purchase them before next Tuesday and take advantage of the preorder discount. This offer will expire next week when the games go live.<br>

	<br>

	We mentioned last week that we''d be giving people a sneak peek at the two new models coming to <i>Counter-Strike: Source</i> this month, and hopefully these don''t disappoint. Here are the new SAS and Leet Crew posing for the camera.<br>

	<br>

	<a target="_new" href="Feb3.2006/img/sas.jpg"><img src="Feb3.2006/img/sas_thumb.jpg">      </a><a target="_new" href="Feb3.2006/img/leet_krew.jpg"><img src="Feb3.2006/img/leet_krew_thumb.jpg"></a><br>

	<br>

	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Steam, and the Steam logo are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation. All other trademarks are property of their respective owners.</span>

</body>

</html>

');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('Feb4.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"
        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">
		<title>Steam - New Counter-Strike: Source Map Coming Soon</title>
		<link href="message12.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen">
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="steamMessage">
		<h1>
		Friday, February 4 2005</h1>
		<br>
Over the next month or so there will be a couple of interesting releases via Steam, in addition to the upcoming Counter-Strike map cs_compound.<br>
<br>
First, we''ll be releasing an update to Half-Life 2: Deathmatch that will include the Slam, Stunstick, and the Crowbar. We''re not ready to release the contest winning maps just yet, but we will be releasing a new map we''ve built at Valve to tide people over while we sort out the contest winners. There will also be a release to Counter-Strike: Source around the same time that will address a few minor issues.<br>
<br>
One feature that we''ll be adding to the Source engine in the coming months is high dynamic range lighting. To showcase this we''ve taken a part of the Highway 17 chapter of Half-Life 2 and worked it into a single level that incorporates HDR along with some new gameplay. We''re calling this short level "The Lost Coast," and it will be made available free of charge to Half-Life 2 customers that meet a specific set of high end hardware requirements. We''ll be publishing those requirements soon.<br>
<br>
Below are a few early concept sketches of the level early in its development.<br>
<br>
		<a target="_new" href="Feb4.2005/img/lost_coast_01.jpg"><img src="Feb4.2005/img/lost_coast_01.gif"></a>
		<a target="_new" href="Feb4.2005/img/lost_coast_02.jpg"><img src="Feb4.2005/img/lost_coast_02.gif"></a>
		<a target="_new" href="Feb4.2005/img/lost_coast_03.jpg"><img src="Feb4.2005/img/lost_coast_03.gif"></a>
		<a target="_new" href="Feb4.2005/img/lost_coast_04.jpg"><img src="Feb4.2005/img/lost_coast_04.gif"></a>
		<br>
		<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Half-Life, and Counter-Strike are trademarks<br>and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation.&nbsp;</span>
