');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('Feb11.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en">

	<head>

		<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

		<title>Steam - New Counter-Strike: Source Map Coming Soon</title>

		<link href="message12.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen">

	</head>

	<body>

		<div class="steamMessage">

		<h1>

		Friday, February 11 2005</h1>

		<br>

		In advance of the Counter-Strike: Source update we''ve mentioned here recently, we''ll be releasing an update for Half-Life 2: Deathmatch. This update will include two new weapons (the StunStick and the Slam) as well as a return of the trusty crowbar. We''ve decided to also include a new map called "Steam Lab."<br>

		<br>

		Here are a few images:<br>

		<br>

		<a target="_new" href="Feb11.2005/img/steamlab_1.jpg"><img src="Feb11.2005/img/steamlab_1_small.jpg"></a>

		<a target="_new" href="Feb11.2005/img/steamlab_2.jpg"><img src="Feb11.2005/img/steamlab_2_small.jpg"></a>

		<a target="_new" href="Feb11.2005/img/steamlab_3.jpg"><img src="Feb11.2005/img/steamlab_3_small.jpg"></a>

		<a target="_new" href="Feb11.2005/img/steamlab_4.jpg"><img src="Feb11.2005/img/steamlab_4_small.jpg"></a>

		<br><br>

		Right around the same time, we''ll be releasing the source code to Half-Life 2: Deathmatch in the SDK.<br>

		<br>

		This release will happen some time next week. Right now, we''re shooting for Thursday the 17th.<br>

		<br>

		And just a quick note for those of you who have been asking -- <em>yes, VAC 2 is coming</em>.<br>

		<br>

		<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Half-Life, and Counter-Strike are trademarks<br>and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation.&nbsp;</span>

		</div>

	</body>



</html>



































');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('Feb17.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"
        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">
		<title>Steam - Today''s update: HL2 deathmatch content, source code. Next week, CS:S.</title>
		<link href="message12.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen">
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="steamMessage">
		<h1>
		Thursday, February 17 2005</h1>
		<br>
		At approximately 4:00 pm PST we''ll be releasing an update that primarily focuses on Half-Life 2: Deathmatch. This update will include the addition of the Stunstick, SLAM, and the Crowbar. It will also include a new original map made by Valve, called Steamlab.<br>
		<br>
		Along with the update to the game, we''ll be releasing the source code for Half-Life 2: Deathmatch in an update to the Source SDK, which should give our MOD community a wide range of functionality they can use to build their games. We''re all excited to see what is built based off of it. The update to the SDK will also allow MOD developers to write their own custom shaders, which will lead to some unique visuals in their games.<br>
		<br>
		Looking ahead to next week, we''re still on track for the Counter-Strike update, which will include a new map called cs_compound, along with a number of smaller changes and bug fixes.<br>
		<br>
		<br>
		<br>
		<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Half-Life, and Counter-Strike are trademarks<br>and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation.&nbsp;</span>
		</div>
	</body>

</html>

















');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('Feb23.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"
        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">
		<title>Steam - Update</title>
		<link href="message12.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen">
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="steamMessage">
		<h1>
		Wednesday, February 23 2005</h1>
		<br>
		We''re still on track for releasing an update to Counter-Strike: Source tomorrow.<br>
		<br>
		While we''ve been talking for a number of weeks about the new hostage rescue map we''ve been working on (cs_compound), Turtle Rock Studios has also been working on getting de_train converted over to Counter-Strike: Source. Along with cs_compound, we''ll be including the new version of de_train in tomorrow''s release.<br>
		<br>
		Along with the two new maps, there are a number of fixes to the bots in Counter-Strike, an enhancement to the radar to display your current location in the map, and a fix for Half-Life 2: Deathmatch where players are disguising themselves as headcrabs, filing cabinets, and other invalid models.<br>
		<br>
		Here''s a preview of de_train:<br>
		<br>
		<a target="_new" href="Feb23.2005/img/de_train1.jpg"><img src="Feb23.2005/img/de_train1_small.jpg"></a>
		<a target="_new" href="Feb23.2005/img/de_train2.jpg"><img src="Feb23.2005/img/de_train2_small.jpg"></a>

<br>
		<br>
		<br>
		<br>
		<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Half-Life, and Counter-Strike are trademarks<br>and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation.&nbsp;</span>
		</div>
	</body>

</html>

















');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('February10.2006', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>

	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

	<title>Steam - Update</title>

	<link href="message10.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> 

</head>

<body>

	<div class="steamMessage">

	<h1>Friday, February 10 2006</h1><Br>

	<a href="steam://openurl/http://www.steampowered.com/index.php?area=dodFreeWeekend">Day of Defeat: Source free weekend</a> is currently underway, so if you''d like to check it out and you haven''t yet, this weekend is your chance. Until Midnight PST on Sunday February 12th, you can play the full version of the game for free. Just double-click on the game in your Steam games list. Right now, there are close to five times the normal number of people playing, so it shouldn''t be hard to find a good match.<br>

	<br>

	<a href="steam://openurl/http://www.steampowered.com/index.php?area=dodFreeWeekend"><img width="220" height="129" src="February10.2006/img/DoDS.gif"></a> &nbsp; <a href="steam://openurl/http://www.steampowered.com/index.php?area=dodFreeWeekend"><img width="220" height="129" src="February10.2006/img/DoDS2.gif"></a><br>

	<br>

	<hr>

	<br>

	<a href="steam://openurl/http://www.sinepisodes.com/index.php?downloads"><img style="position:relative;left:-4px;" src="February10.2006/img/SiiiiiiiiN.gif" align="left"></a>The Sin Episodes web site has been updated, and they''ve released a new trailer for their game to check out. If you haven''t seen it already, head on over to <a href="steam://openurl/http://www.sinepisodes.com/index.php?downloads">their downloads site</a>. Looks like they are just about ready to get their first episode out the door. <br>

	<br>

	<br>

	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Steam, and the Steam logo are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation. All other trademarks are property of their respective owners.</span>

</body>



</html>

');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('February17.2006', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>

	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

	<title>Steam - Update</title>

	<link href="message13.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> 

</head>

<body>

	<center>

	<div class="steamMessage">

	<h1>Friday, February 17 2006</h1><br>

	<b>Day of Defeat Free Weekend</b> was a huge hit last weekend -- thanks to everyone who took part. Thanks also to all the new players who took the time to send us feedback about the experience of playing DoD:S for the first time. As always, we have more in store for the DoD:S community; we''re currently working on some pretty interesting new content for the game, which we''ll talk about in the coming weeks.<br>

	<br>	

	<hr>

	<br>

	<img width="385" height="70" src="February17.2006/img/RedOrchestraLogo.gif" style="margin-left:-8px;"><br>

	<i>Red Orchestra: Ostfront 41-45</i> from Tripwire Interactive will debut on Steam next month, and is currently available for pre-purchase and pre-loading. Red Orchestra is a realistic online action game set in the Russian front of WWII that features thirteen scenarios, an arsenal of twenty-four weapons, and fourteen drivable vehicles including tanks and armored transports. In its March 2006 issue, PC Zone UK says Red Orchestra "touts a finely tuned balance of amazing gameplay and surprising realism." <a href="steam://openurl/http://storefront.steampowered.com/video/RedOrchestra_Trailer.wmv">Check out the RO: 41-45 trailer</a> and if the game looks like it''s up your alley, go ahead and <a href="steam://preload/1200">preload it now</a>.<br>

	<br>

	<br>

	<br>

	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Steam, and the Steam logo are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation. All other trademarks are property of their respective owners.</span><br>

</center>

</body>



</html>

');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('February24.2006', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>

	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

	<title>Steam - Update</title>

	<link href="message13.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> 

</head>

<body>

	<center>

	<div class="steamMessage">

	<h1>Friday, February 24 2006</h1><br>

	As we''ve <a href="steam://openurl/http://www.steampowered.com/Steam/Marketing/April15.2005/">mentioned before</a>, we''ve been hard at work on the continuation of Half-Life 2 for some time now. Soon, as part of the upcoming Half-Life 2: Episode One, you''ll find out about what happened to the Citadel after the end of HL2, what happened to your nemesis Breen, and how Alyx managed to survive the explosion at the game''s end. You''ll also learn a lot more about Alyx, since nearly the entire episode is spent with her at your side.   <br>

	<br>

	<a href="steam://openurl/http://steampowered.com/Steam/Marketing/February24.2006/img/HL2_EP1_Alyx_Silhouette1.jpg"><img src="February24.2006/img/HL2_EP1_Alyx_Silhouette1_s.jpg"></a><br>

	<br>

	During the development of Half-Life 2, we at Valve were frustrated at how long it took us (six years!) to ship the game. With that in mind , the decision was made to try an episodic approach to the next Half-Life products, each  designed to reveal new story, gameplay, and the latest Source technology in four to six hour experiences.<br>

	<br>

	Over the coming weeks, we''ll keep you informed about the game''s status. For now, head over to Computer and Video Games site to read <a href="steam://openurl/http://www.computerandvideogames.com/r/?page=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/interviews/interviews_story.php?id=134751">an interview with Valve''s Robin Walker</a> about Episode One.<br>

	<br>

	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Half-Life, Steam, and the Steam logo are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation.</span><br>

</center>

</body>



</html>

');
