INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('September2.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>

	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

	<title>Steam - Update</title>

	<link href="message22.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> </head>

	<base target="_new">

<body>



	<div class="steamMessage">



	<h1>Friday, September 2 2005</h1>

	<br>

	Day of Defeat: Source will be released this month. While we''re not quite ready to pin down the exact date of when it will be available to play, we are confident that it will happen in September. Once we do have an exact date and time for when the game will be activated, we''ll let everyone know.<br>

	<br>

	There will be a period of one week at minimum during which people will be able to pre-order and preload the game via Steam, giving them the ability to unlock and play at the moment it is activated.<br>

	<br>

	Day of Defeat: Source will be available as an individual purchase via Steam, as well as part of the Counter-Strike: Source retail package that will be available at stores around the same time. Half-Life 2: Silver and Gold package customers will automatically be able to play.<br>

	<br>

	In the meantime, here are two of the player models from the game -- the Allied Rifleman and the Axis Panzerschreck.<br>

	<br>

	<a href="September2.2005/img/allies_rifleman.jpg"><img src="September2.2005/img/allies_rifleman_thumb.jpg"></a>

	<a href="September2.2005/img/axis_panzer.jpg"><img src="September2.2005/img/axis_panzer_thumb.jpg"></a>

	<br>

	<br>

	<br>

	<br>

	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Half-Life, Counter-Strike, Day of Defeat, and Source are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation.</span>

	</div>

</body>



</html>





');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('September9.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>

	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

	<title>Steam - Update</title>

	<link href="message23.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> </head>

	<base target="_new">

<body>



	<div class="steamMessage">



	<h1>Friday, September 9 2005</h1>

	Preloading of Day of Defeat: Source will begin next week. It will be released and ready to play on September 26th. Once we get closer to that date, we''ll set an exact time for when we''ll "throw the switch." <br>

	<br>

	Preloading the game allows people to have the entire game on their hard drive in encrypted form so that, if already purchased or pre-ordered, it will be playable at the moment it is released. Dedicated server administrators will also have some time to get their servers up and running before the 26th.<br>

	<hr>

	There is also some pretty exciting news on the MOD front, where the team over at Dystopia is preparing to release a demo of their game today at 11:59 GMT. Head on over to <a href="http://www.dystopia-game.com ">the Dystopia page</a> to check out their release.

	</div>

	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Half-Life, Counter-Strike, <br>Day of Defeat, and Source are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation.</span>



</body>



</html>





');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('September16.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>

	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

	<title>Steam - Update</title>

	<link href="message22.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> </head>

<body>



	<div class="steamMessage">



	<h1>Friday, September 16 2005</h1>

	<br>

	The preload for Day of Defeat: Source is in full swing now. There is still plenty of time for everyone to <b><a href="steam://preload/300">pre-load the game</a></b> before it is made available on September 26th at 3:00 pm PDT. (If you''re unsure of what time this is for you locally, you can <a target="_new" href="http://www.worldtimeserver.com/convert_time_in_US-WA.aspx?y=2005&mo=9&d=26&h=15&mn=0">convert to your local time zone here</a>.)<br>

	<br>

	We''re also planning a release for next week that will update the Source engine to the same version used for Day of Defeat: Source. There are a number of small fixes contained in this release that we''ll cover in detail when it''s closer to release time.<br>

	<br>

	Have a look at two more of the character models from Day of Defeat: Source -- the Allied bazooka class and the Axis sniper class:<br>

	<br><br>

	<a target="_new" href="September16.2005/img/allies_rocket.jpg"><img src="September16.2005/img/allies_rocket_thumb.jpg"></a> &nbsp;

	<a target="_new" href="September16.2005/img/axis_sniper.jpg"><img src="September16.2005/img/axis_sniper_thumb.jpg"></a><br>

	<br><br><br><br>

	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Half-Life, Counter-Strike, Day of Defeat, and Source are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation.</span>

	</div>

</body>



</html>





');
INSERT INTO marketing (msgtype, language, content) VALUES ('September23.2005', 'english', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN"

        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en"> <head>

	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1">

	<title>Steam - Update</title>

	<link href="message22.css" rel="stylesheet" media="screen"> </head>

	<base target="_new">

<body>



	<div class="steamMessage">



	<h1>Friday, September 23 2005</h1>

	<br>

	Day of Defeat: Source is ready and we''re set to make it available on Monday, September 26, at 3 pm PDT. For those who have not yet pre-purchased the game, the 10% pre-purchase discount offer ends when it is released.<br>

	<br>

	In addition to pre-loading DoD: Source, another good thing to do in preparation of its release is to update your video card driver. With HDR and other advanced features included, DoD: Source pushes the limits of the Source engine a bit harder than other Source games. Check over at <a href=http://www.nvidia.com>NVIDIA</a> or <a href=http://www.ati.com>ATI</a> website for driver updates, depending on your hardware.<br>

	<br>

	Day of Defeat: Source will be available as an individual purchase via Steam, as well as part of the Counter-Strike: Source retail package that will be available at stores around the same time. Half-Life 2: Silver and Gold package customers will automatically be able to play.<br>

	<br>

	Finally, as we await the game''s arrival, IGN.com posted a <a href=http://pc.ign.com/articles/652/652450p1.html>preview</a> this week with a large collection of DoD: Source shots and video footage. Full reviews will be appearing beginning this weekend and web sites and in game magazines.<br>

	<br>

	<br>



	<br>

	<span class="footer">&copy; Valve Corporation. All rights reserved. Valve, Half-Life, Counter-Strike, Day of Defeat, and Source are trademarks and/or registered trademarks of Valve Corporation.</span>

	</div>

</body>



</html>





');
